SIMPLE: ungainly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ungainly
<hw>Un*gain"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>ungeinliche</ets>,
adv., fr. <ets>ungein</ets> inconvenient; <ets>un-</ets> + Icel.
<ets>gegn</ets> ready, serviceable; adv., against, opposite. See
<er>Un-</er> not, and <er>Gain</er>, <pos>a.</pos>,
<er>Again</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not gainly; not expert or dexterous; clumsy;
awkward; uncouth; <as>as, an <ex>ungainly</ex> strut in
walking</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>ungainly</qex> figure and eccentric manners.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unsuitable; unprofitable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hammond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ungainly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ungainly
<hw>Un*gain"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an ungainly
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ungear</ent>⟦br⟧
